ξ 8. prospectus. A fanciful pictuse, which is hardly borne out by facts. as no such view can be obtained near the summit of the Mont Genevre, nor indeed of any other of the pasees. The description of Polybius does not imply any such actual view of the plains of Lombardy, for his word ἐνάργεια may mean ¹ evidence ’ or ⁶ proof' addressed to the reason, and not to the sight.
